  "texts": [
    "This scheme assumes that the communication users are located in the sidelobe region, and the transmitted beampattern is changed from pulse to pulse according to the embedded communication symbols, while keeping the mainlobe towards the target of interest [39].",
    "For example, the communication symbols can be represented by different side lobe levels (SLLs) toward the communication direction.",
    "Moreover, the main lobes of different beam patterns are almost the same, guaranteeing satisfactory detection performance.",
    "This information embedding approach can be considered AM in the spatial domain [40].",
    "Besides AM, PM [43] and QAM [41] are two other popular signaling strategies."
  ],
